   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LESSON THREE GOD'S INTENTION IN MAN Scripture Reading: Gen 2:8-9, 16-17; Rev 2:7; 22:14; John 6:35a, 57b OUTLINE Two choices remaining in front of man: The tree of life: Signifying God as life to man.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Issuing in a dependent life.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The tree of knowledge: Signifying Satan as evil to man.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Issuing in an independent life.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>God wanting man to receive Him as life by the way of eating: Eating being the unique way to receive nourishment organically.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>God being man's real food.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To receive God by eating being to have God assimilated into man's being metabolically.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>God forbidding man to eat the tree of knowledge: God's first commandment to man.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Eating to receive something in being critical to man: After man was created, God not asking man to do anything.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>God only charging man not to eat wrongly.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>To eat the tree of knowledge being to receive Satan as an evil life into man's being.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>God's forbidding commandment being a warning to man: Indicating God's greatness in dealing with man.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Indicating God's love to man.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Indicating God's desire that man would eat the tree of life to receive God into him as his life.</S>
   </TEXT>
